        • [ - ] Olympic2008 - member since 15-Jul-11

          Leicester fell to the foot of the table after another away defeat at QPR. However they have only suffered a solitary defeat at home picking up seven points from six home matches. Liverpool have already tasted defeat four time on the road in the league this season and are a pale imitation of the team that were so entertaining last season (even the most ardent red will testify to that). The simple fact is they have tried to integrate too many players into the team and this has not worked out, many will point to the fact they have missed the goals of Suarez and Sturridge which is certainly true. Nevertheless when they have started with nine or more of the players that were part of the squad last season they have picked up nine points from four games. With less than that number of starters just they have managed eight points from nine games. Is Brendan Rogers the new 'tinker man'? Or has just added numbers rather than quality to his team?
